<item>
            <title>[LANG-74] [lang] [patch] ArrayUtils.addAll doesn&apos;t always return new array</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-74</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;according to the javadoc of the ArrayUtils.addAll() method, a new array is&lt;br/&gt;
returned. However, if 1 of the 2 given arrays is null, the not-null array is&lt;br/&gt;
returned (and not a new array).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;attached are a fix and a junit test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maarten&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
